# Precision approach (wall_aligner.py): creep straight toward (or away from)
# the face in front until the perpendicular distance to the LIVE fitted line
# equals `distance`. Yaw is re-servoed square on the live lidar fit every
# cycle — the robot stays perpendicular to the REAL surface the whole drive —
# and lateral position is held on odom. Slow speeds, bidirectional final
# correction and a stationary multi-scan verification give cm-level precision.
#
# Requires the robot to already be square (AlignToWall first); aborts if the
# face reads more than ~5 deg off. Direct cmd_vel — bypasses Nav2 and the
# costmaps, keep it short and use it only against the intended surface.
float32 distance    # target perpendicular distance (m), same measure AlignToWall reports
float32 max_travel  # m; > 0 caps the total displacement (safety), 0 = node default
---
bool success
string error
float32 traveled        # signed forward displacement actually driven (m)
float32 final_distance  # stationary-verified distance at finish (m)
